postcontent: Franchi SPAS 12 shotgun. This is an early version, with an unaltered factory recalled, "paddle” style safety. Shotgun has the factory folding stock with, original one-handed, " hook". These shotguns were made famous by such movies as, "The Terminator" and, "Jurassic Park". Shotgun fires 2 3/4" 12 GA. Can fired either pump action or semi auto with the flip of a switch.Only roughly 1600 were ever imported into the US before multiple crime bills in the late 80's and early 90's banned any future import. Legal to own in NC. I purchased this shotgun from a FFL in Raleigh around 14 years ago. Shotgun is in excellent condition. I have not fired it in years, however it cycled flawlessly the last time I shot it. Kept in climate controlled safe for years, cleaned and oiled twice a year.  I purchased this shotgun to, "scratch an itch". Enjoyed it, has been an interesting conversation piece. Shotgun is just taking up valuable space in the safe. Rather someone else enjoy it like I have. Weapon is complete. No box or any other accessories. title: For Sale:  CVC Classic Sporter 12ga O/U SHOTGUN
postcontent: I have for sale a  CVC (CONNECTICUT VALLEY CLASSIC) CLASSIC SPORTER 12 ga 30in barrels w/ 2 site beads, barrel side vents, jeweled mono-bloc & ejectors. Winchokes in both barrels with 2 Briley Extended tubes and 4 flush mount win chokes. satin varnish finish wood. Stainless steel raised side panel receiver with laser engraving, adjustable wide shoe mechanical trigger, non-auto safety, top lever centered. .6” rear recoil pad. AA+ figured wood, flat knob grip. 98% overall condition, with two minor dents in fore grip, used very little. S/N CVF-073. Shotgun comes with a SKB soft case. The only other one I found on the internet they are asking $1695.00 and mine looks far better.                                            CALL MIKE REDACTED A STEAL AT $1200.00  This is a Beautiful great shooting over/under, I'm selling it because i was in an auto accident and can't shoulder it.  What is a CONNECTICUT VALLEY CLASSIC ? When Classic Doubles International discontinued business, the principal owners still believed in the Winchester 101 design and concept. On returning to New England, they formed Connecticut Valley Classics to continue the 101 design in an American made gun. The mechanical design was near identical to the Japanese version; the most significant deviation was changing all threaded parts to American thread sizes, and changing the frame and forend material to 416 stainless steel. Most mechanical parts are, again, directly interchangeable with the Winchester 101 OR the Classic Doubles 101. Competition proved to be too stiff, and stateside costs to high to maintain adequate sales. CVC discontinued operations in about 1997.

Serial number matches on case, barrel, slide, and frame.Unlike laser sights that attach to a pistol's exterior, this LaserMax sight sits inside your firearm's recoil spring – replacing the spring guide and plug. The on/off switch replaces the slide stop lever. That means the sight is an integrated part of your pistol that won't be affected by drops or bumps. It also ensures absolute alignment with the bore for consistent point-of-aim. Constructed of high-strength aircraft aluminum with a weather-resistant, sealed BK-7 window glass projection port, it projects a pulsing red-orange 5mW, 635 nM laser beam onto the target. Because the laser is internal, your firearm can be carried and drawn from its usual holster without any modifications. It also frees up the accessory rail on pistols equipped with one so that a separate light or accessory can still be mounted. Power is supplied by three silver-oxide watch batteries.  Five-year limited warranty.
